MatchedRegions.transcript: Therefore, we propose CarLane, the first three-way simple real-world domain adaptation benchmark for 2D lane detection, which allows single and multi-target, unsupervised domain adaptation.
We train several well-known user methods to establish baselines, including our own method.
Templation of the methods, baseline rates, as well as tools for data collection and labeling are publicly available.

MatchedRegion.Text: To the best of our knowledge, we are the first to adapt a lane detection model from simulation to multiple real-world domains
